eet are gonna shatter that illusion of fantasy tootsweet! <br><br>As an EQ newbie, I created my 1st (and still only) character; a halfling Cleric. My RL friend who got me into the game ported his lvl 60 druid to Rivervale to meet me. I was very excited about exploring the area &amp; getting a feel for the game, but my friend said immidiately &quot;Ok, come on...we gotta go power-level ya!&quot; <br><br>Well, ok, I thought. A couple quick early levels will only help me to be able to explore more on my own, etc. SO we went &amp; boosted me to around L5 or 6 when I told him I wanted to go explore more of the area around Misty &amp; fight some goblins &amp; such. His response was one of pure shock: &quot;But why? We gotta get you leveled &amp; get you some uber-armour so you can get out &amp; play the GAME!&quot; <br><br>This is the part that, no matter how open-minded I try to be, I just don't understand. Why can't EQ just be fun? Meaning, what the hell are you people out there power-leveling for? ESPECIALLY you fellow newbs? Isn't there a ton of things that you are missing out on never being able to fight? A ton of places that go unexplored? Why should you sit in one place for hours being PL'd &amp; killing the SAME reds over &amp; over when there is a dungeon nearby that is tailor-made for you to adventure in? What are you working towards? <br><br>I understand we'd all like to kill emporers &amp; gods one day, but it seems like to many people, the early &amp; mid game are just completely passed over in an attempt to LEVEL LEVEL LEVEL ASAP! If I had listened to my friend &amp; had him take me to Oasis at L8-9 or LOIO at 10-15 to be PL'd, I'd have never gotten to explore Befallen &amp; test my faith &amp; steel againt the unholy legions within; I'd have never gotten to know all the NPC's in my town or gotten to strike fear into the hearts of Runnyeye goblins. I would have missed all these wonderful adventures I've had just because I was worried that I wouldn't level fast enough. <br><br>There is so much content &amp; so much to see; what is the difference between fighting a Gorge Minotaur at lvl 12 &amp; fighting Giants at 45? It's the exact same situation, and boy would I have been dissappointed if the first time I came upon that Gorge Minotaur he was green because I had been killing Red Knolls in one spot for 600 hours while getting SOT'd &amp; SLN'd by the LVL 60 Druid behind me. That, to me, is not fun. Adventuring &amp; exploring &amp; playing the game are fun; and I'm so glad I didn't miss out on any of the low-end content. When I did slay my first dragon, it was so sweet in part because I had earned it; and further on down the road, while we're all sitting in the Plane of Justice medding up, I imagine I'll have quite a few more interesting stories to tell than some will. Unless you find stories of mathematic equations &amp; dmg/dly comparisons etc. interesting...I personally don't.<br><br>Just my two cents worth, but I really am curious to hear from people who play from this perspective. Enlighten me, and maybe I won't be so annoyed when I meet you in the game. <br><br>-Twosheds Tuggins <br>-L48 Cleric of The Order of Bristlebane <br>-Rivervale, Antonica<br><br>P.S. I do realize that many people play alternates and, having done it all before, they feel no need to do it all again &amp; just want to get their character to a LVL that is useful to them. This is a different situation than I am talking about, so please don't respond with that explanation if you don't mind ) Thanks.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ucaeanthepaladin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CaeanthePaladin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/29/02 7:43:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2933.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://caean.20fr.com/Caean2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why the powergaming mindset?</span><hr size=1> some people have friends who are high level. They want to play with them and experience the game with them.<br><br>Other people are leveling because their guild needs a particular class, such as a cleric, or a warrior.<br><br>Other people just have no appreciation for the process and want to get to the &quot;end&quot; of the game, without realizing that no such thing exists.<br><br>The bottom line is they at least think they're having fun, or think that if they do this, they will have fun at a later time.<br><br>The truth is, if you don't enjoy the lower levels, you'll probably never enjoy the higher levels. That's why you see a ton of people 2 and 3-boxing. They can kill, get exp quickly in their non raiding times, then go raid and enjoy that.<br><br>2-boxing is entirely another issue, which in my opinion has killed the pickup group completely. Between guild groups and 2-boxing not much is left for the casual player who just wants some exp.  <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=36323 ">Caean Sacroguerre, Knight of Tunare</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/bayonaero.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=friday>Friday</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local Resident</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/29/02 8:02:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2933.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Heh</span><hr size=1> Everquest is what you make it.<br><br>I have been playing since beta, and while i had no one to power level me (because few people were more then 4 levels above me) i still pushed foward each day to become more powerful.<br><br>Why is that? Because with out my levels, i would not have been one of the first people to explore Lower Guk, and i would not have been able to be present at the first server wide Caizic Thule slaying.<br><br>While that may not be important to many people, it is and always has been to me. <br><br>My advise to you is this, dont be concerned with what other people do. Play the game in whatever form it is that makes it enjoyable to you and helps you get the most out of it. <br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ubdnightfall.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BD Nightfall</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/29/02 8:28:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2933.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Heh</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  a friend who swore to me that EQ was more than just hack &amp; slash &amp; stats<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Heh, you can also do tradeskills and quests....which involve hack and slash somewhere... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/bayonaero.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=varulvthewarrior>Varulv the Warrior</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/29/02 9:28:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2933.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Heh</span><hr size=1> I powergamed to join Welas, the only one I knew in RL who played this game.<br><br>He was a 57 druid and to be able to play with him I got powerleveled. What I missed