 give me stuff or drag me someplace where we would stand in one place and kill mobs while some L 50 druid or enchanter would babysit us.  Talk about boring!  So Faervas and I resolved that we weren't going to let the game be 'ruined' for us, and made an effort to find other people who were also new to the game to play with, or who were at least willing to explore, and make messy mistakes in, exotic places.  A year and a half later, we have friends in our little resultant guild with mains from level 13-55; and while we have crawled at least part of all of the old world dungeons, most of the newer ones in our level range, and are about to take our first all guild group to Sebilis, we have mains who are just now doing Unrest and Najena, so we try very hard to let those who are just starting to learn the game, or are very casual players, enjoy the game at their own pace.  <br><br>I personally don't get, either, people who 'rush' the levelling/item acquisition process; in my mind, they are only cheating themselves out of a big part of the joy of the game.  It *does* suck some when you are in small guild and you can't offer your friends much other than a good time because the item economy in the game is so screwed up.  In that regard the Luclin Twilight quests have been a godsend, as they are something that most of our folks can help with, and that we get a sense of accomplishment (and some spiffy, unique stuff!) out of doing.   But some folks are always going to have the linear, 'beat the game' kind of mindset, even in a very open-ended game like EQ, and well, all I can say is 'different strokes for different folks...<br><br>Regards,<br>Nydia Ywalmoriel<br>Autonomous Collective<br><br>P.S.  Some of the best times I have ever had in the game have been in Runnyeye, especially just post-revamp. <br>One night, even with Endure Magic on him, our (halfling druid) puller was coming back charmed about every other pull, and we would watch him run to the corner, turn towards us, and his little hands light up, as he proceeded to nuke the crap out of us <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/urolielkotn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RolielKotN</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/30/02 2:38:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2933.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why the powergaming mindset?</span><hr size=1> EQ is pretty hack and slash, but the hack and slash is pretty in-depth. <p><IMG SRC=http://www.tiannathomas.com/images/roliel3.gif><small><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uapocc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Apocc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/30/02 2:11:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2933.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why the powergaming mindset?</span><hr size=1> Well as for me, since working with my main after a very long time trying to figure what class and race I want to play. I'll always try to lvl but most of the time I use trying to build my trade skills. That too is a quest in itself. It will make you go out and work on certain criterias, lvling, other trades and look for certain items. <br><br> <p><b>Apocalyse Evermore</b><br>~<i>Knight of time's past</i> ~<br>~<i>Evil of Future's present</i>~<br><br>"All ogres are not ugly & dumb, and I shall prove it..."<br>"You will watch as I bathe in